Brmlab TETRA listener.

This software is collection of tools which automates recieving and decoding
audio from TETRA downlink channels.

== build
  * clone this repository
  * update submdules

git submodule init
git submodule update

  * install required dependencies
    * libosmocore
    * gnuradio (>=3.7.5)
    * gr-osmosdr
    * python3

  * (download and) build
./build

== usage
  * edit config in file radio-tetra/config.sh
  * execute radio-tetra/tetra.sh to start reciever
  * execute radio-tetra/tetra_cli_pwr.py to list singnal strenght on channels
  * execute radio-tetra/tetra_cli_auto_tune.py N to allow automatic fine tunning
    N should be channel with good signal-strenght ration

